{"lemma":"شِعْرُ","slug":"شِعْرُ","root":"ش.ع.ر","root_slug":"ش-ع-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ع-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شِعْر","root":"شعر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":19},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22464","n22468","n22469","n22470","n22471","n22472"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%90%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to know, to have knowledge, to be cognizant","examples":[{"text":"وَإِذَا قِيلَ لَهُمْ لَا تُفْسِدُوا فِي الْأَرْضِ قَالُوا إِنَّمَا نَحْنُ مُصْلِحُونَ ۝ أَلَا إِنَّهُمْ هُمُ الْمُفْسِدُونَ وَلَٰكِنْ لَا يَشْعُرُونَ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to realize, to notice, to come to know"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to perceive, to feel, to sense"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be conscious, to be aware"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make or compose poetry"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to poetize, to versify"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become a poet","examples":[{"text":"خَالَطَ الشُّعَرَاءَ فَشَعُرَ","english":"He mingled with the poets and became a poet"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to perceive, to feel, to sense"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become aware"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hair","examples":[{"text":"لَقَدْ كُنْتُ أَزْرَعُ شَعْرَ جَسْدِي مُنْذُ بُضِعِ سَنَوَاتٍ حَتَّى الْآنَ.","english":"I've been growing my hair for a few years now."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bristles"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fur, pelt"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cracks, hairline cracks (in a vase)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tomfoolery, mumbo-jumbery, bobbins","tags":["Egypt","colloquial"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have thick and long hair, to be hirsute"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"knowing, knowledge","examples":[{"text":"لَيْتَ شِعْرِي","english":"I wish I knew"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"noticing, perception, sensation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"poetry, poem, verses"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of شِعَار (šiʕār)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *śaʕr- (“hair”).\nCognate with Hebrew שיער (se'ár).\n\nCompare Hebrew שיר (shir) and Hebrew שירה (shirá)."},"ipa":["/ʃa.ʕa.ra/","/ʃa.ʕar/","/ʃiʕr/","/ʃu.ʕur/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22464","headword_ar":"شعّر","root":"$Er","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"as an intrans. verb: see 4: ―         -b2-  and as a trans. verb also: see 4."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n22468","headword_ar":"شَعْرٌ","root":"$Er","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEarN","text_ar":"شَعَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb, K, but only the latter in my copies of the S and in the O,) two wellknown dial. vars., the like being common in cases of this kind, in which the medial radical letter is a faucial, (MF,) [but the latter I have found to be the more common,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what grows upon the body, that is not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suwf","text_ar":"صُوف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabar","text_ar":"وَبَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) it is an appertenance"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of human beings and of other animals:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb:) [when spoken of as used in the fabrication of cloth for tents &c., the meaning intended is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats' hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 4 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] of the masc. gender: (Msb, TA:) pl. (of the former, Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEuwrN","text_ar":"شُعُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (of the latter, Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oEaArN","text_ar":"اَشْعَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and (of the latter also, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEaArN","text_ar":"شِعَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^u$ayoEaArN","text_ar":"اُشَيْعَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", properly dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oEaArN","text_ar":"اَشْعَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is used, accord. to Aboo-Ziyád, as dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEuwrN","text_ar":"شُعُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, * Msb, K:) and this, i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEorapN","text_ar":"شَعْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEarahN","text_ar":"شَعَرَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], is also used metonymically as a pl. (K, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoniY wabayonaka AlmaAlu $aq~u Al$~aEorapi","text_ar":"بَيْنِى وَبَيْنَكَ المَالُ شَقُّ الشَّعْرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~u AlA^ubolumapi","text_ar":"شَقُّ الاُبْلُمَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The property is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be, equally divided between me and thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aY fulaAnN Al$~aEorapa","text_ar":"رَاَى فُلَانٌ الشَّعْرَةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one saw,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has seen, hoariness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white hairs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yaakoob, S, A, TA,) upon his head. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [The n. un.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEorapN","text_ar":"شَعْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used, metonymically, as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A daughter."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEarN","text_ar":"شَعَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, and so accord. to the TA, but in the CK ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEorN","text_ar":"شُعْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",) signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Plants"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) as being likened to hair. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And the same, (A, K, TA, but in the CK ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEorN","text_ar":"شُعْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Saffron"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before it is pulverized."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)"}],"source_refs":["MF","S","A","Msb","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n22469","headword_ar":"شُعْرٌ","root":"$Er","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next two preceding sentences."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n22470","headword_ar":"شِعْرٌ","root":"$Er","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[an inf. n., (see 1, first sentence,) and used as a simple subst. signifying]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Knowledge; cognizance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge of the minute particulars of things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perception by means of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the senses."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layota","text_ar":"لَيْتَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEoriY fulaAnFA maA SanaEa","text_ar":"شِعْرِى فُلَانًا مَا صَنَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ks, Lh, S, * Msb, * K, *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layota $iEoriY lahu maA SanaEa","text_ar":"لَيْتَ شِعْرِى لَهُ مَا صَنَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layota $iEoriY Eanohu maA SanaEa","text_ar":"لَيْتَ شِعْرِى عَنْهُ مَا صَنَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ks, Lh, K, *) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Would that I knew what such a one did,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has done;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K, * Msb, * TA;) for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"would that my knowledge were present at,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comprehending, what such a one did,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has done;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the phrase being elliptical: (TA:) accord. to Sb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layota $iEoriY","text_ar":"لَيْتَ شِعْرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lyt $iEoratiY","text_ar":"ليت شِعْرَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being elided as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^abuw Eu*orihaA","text_ar":"هُوَ اَبُو عُذْرِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hw Abw Eu*oratihaA","text_ar":"هو ابو عُذْرَتِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, TA,) the elision of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this latter instance, as Sb says, being peculiar to the case of the words being preceded by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abw","text_ar":"ابو"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orapN","text_ar":"عُذْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iqaAmap","text_ar":"اـِقَامَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"when used as a prefixed noun; though"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layota $iEoratiY","text_ar":"لَيْتَ شِعْرَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not now known to have been heard. (TA.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layota $iEoriY maA kaAna","text_ar":"لَيْتَ شِعْرِى مَا كَانَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Would that I knew what happened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has happened."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b2-  The predominant signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEorN","text_ar":"شِعْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Poetry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"verse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K;) because of its preeminence by reason of the measure and the rhyme; though every kind of knowledge is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEorN","text_ar":"شِعْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or because it relates the minute affairs of the Arabs, and the occult particulars of their secret affairs, and their facetiæ: (Er-Rághib, TA:) it is properly defined as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"language qualified by rhyme and measure intentionally;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which last restriction excludes the like of the saying in the Kur [xciv. 3 and 4],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aal~a*iY A^anoqaDa Zahorako warafaEonaA laka *ikorako","text_ar":"اَلَّذِى اَنْقَضَ ظَهْرَكْ وَرَفَعْنَا لَكَ ذِكْرَكْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because this is not intentionally qualified by rhyme and measure: (KT; and the like is said in the Msb:) and sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single verse"},{"kind":"text","text":"is thus termed: (Akh, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oEaArN","text_ar":"اَشْعَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Falsehood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the many lies in poetry. (B, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Akh"]},{"entry_id":"n22471","headword_ar":"شَعَرٌ","root":"$Er","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEorN","text_ar":"شَعْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n22472","headword_ar":"شَعِرٌ","root":"$Er","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oEaru","text_ar":"اَشْعَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [The fem.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEirapN","text_ar":"شَعِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [particularly] A sheep or goat ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN","text_ar":"شَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having hair growing between the two halves of its hoof, which in consequence bleed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having an itching in its knees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and therefore always scratching with them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]}}